Note: ============================================================================
Note: Expression Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top of the expression precedence ladder. Delegates to
parse_assignment_expression which is the lowest-precedence
binary-style operator above the comma operator (which JS supports
but we treat as a statement-list construct, not a true binary op).
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse expression (comma operator lowest precedence)

    Return proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Right-associative assignment. Parses a conditional expression
first, then peeks for an assignment operator (=, +=, -=, etc.).
On match, recursively parses another assignment expression as the
right side - the recursion is what gives right-associativity
("a = b = c" parses as "a = (b = c)").
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_assignment_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse assignment expression

    @Reasoning:
    Assignment operators: =, +=, -=, *=, /=, %=, etc.
    Right associative: a = b = c
    @End Reasoning

    @Reasoning:
    Bare single-identifier arrow functions ("x => x", "x => { ... }",
    "async x => x") have no parenthesized parameter list, so the
    parenthesized-arrow path in parse_parenthesized_expression never sees
    them. We detect them here, at assignment precedence (where arrows live
    in the grammar), using two-token lookahead: when current is a lone
    IDENTIFIER immediately followed by "=>", the identifier is the single
    arrow parameter. The "async" prefix is consumed first, then the same
    IDENTIFIER+"=>" shape is required, so "async x => x" flows through the
    identical builder. The lookahead never commits unless "=>" actually
    follows, so ordinary identifier expressions ("x + 1", "x") are
    untouched. Each accepted path consumes at least the identifier and the
    arrow token, guaranteeing forward progress.
    @End Reasoning
    Let lead_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    If lead_type is equal to TOKEN_ASYNC from Lexer:
        Let after_async be proc peek_second_token_type with parser
        If after_async is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let async_arrow_second be proc peek_second_token_type with parser
            If async_arrow_second is equal to TOKEN_ARROW from Lexer:
                Let async_param_name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
                proc advance_token with parser
                Let async_params be proc create from List
                Let async_param_node be proc create_ast_node with JS_PARAM
                proc set_node_name with async_param_node, async_param_name
                proc list_append from List with async_params, async_param_node
                Let async_arrow be proc parse_arrow_function with parser, async_params
                proc set_node_attribute with async_arrow, "async", "true"
                Return async_arrow
            End If
            Note: "async <ident>" not followed by "=>": current is now the
            Note: identifier; fall through to the normal expression chain which
            Note: re-reads current_token, so no token is lost.
        Otherwise:
            If after_async is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
                Note: "async (params) => body" - parenthesized async arrow (the
                Note: canonical form the backend re-emits). Consume "async", then
                Note: let the parenthesized-expression path build the arrow; tag
                Note: the result async only if it actually parsed as an arrow so a
                Note: plain "async(x)" call expression is left untouched.
                proc advance_token with parser
                Let paren_result be proc parse_conditional_expression with parser
                If paren_result is not equal to 0:
                    Let pr_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with paren_result, 0
                    If pr_type is equal to JS_ARROW_FUNCTION:
                        proc set_node_attribute with paren_result, "async", "true"
                    End If
                End If
                Return paren_result
            End If
